Ok, I have approximately *zero* clue if this is even halfways correct. I have no `js` experience whatsoever. I happened to find an instance of `openPopup()` in [search.py](https://github.com/python-visualization/folium/blob/e4663545f243fec09b901936112f32bec6c860bb/folium/plugins/search.py#L68), so I figured it was possible.

I started hunted around in `map.py` for where the popups get added and the [`tooltip` code](https://github.com/python-visualization/folium/blob/master/folium/map.py#L238) in `Marker` caught my eye:

```
{% if this.tooltip %}.bindTooltip("{{this.tooltip.__str__()}}"){% endif %}
```

I just guessed and was able to [get something implemented](https://github.com/jwhendy/folium/blob/open-popup/folium/map.py#L252) in `Popup`:

```
class Popup(Element):
    """Create a Popup instance that can be linked to a Layer.
    Parameters
    ----------

        ### unchanged code removed ###

        self.default_open = default_open

        self._template = Template(u"""
            var {{this.get_name()}} = L.popup({maxWidth: '{{this.max_width}}'});
            {% for name, element in this.html._children.items() %}
                var {{name}} = $('{{element.render(**kwargs).replace('\\n',' ')}}')[0];
                {{this.get_name()}}.setContent({{name}});
            {% endfor %}
            {{this._parent.get_name()}}.bindPopup({{this.get_name()}})
            {% if this.default_open %}.openPopup(){% endif %};
            {% for name, element in this.script._children.items() %}
                {{element.render()}}
            {% endfor %}
        """)  # noqa
```

