@KristofDM the way you add methods to nodes is as follows:

```python

class FooNode(DjangoObjectType):
    my_method_field = graphene.Field(AllergensNode')

    def resolve_my_method_field(instance, args, request, info):
        return instance.allergens
```

a node looks for resolve functions that match the name of the field on them. Thats how they resolve which methods should trigger when a field is accessed.

